{
  "stem": "512.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It didn't matter if you kept to yourself or you went to shower, but if your next-- the person next to you didn't, so you-- a couple hours later, you had it again.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there were no, no warm showers or anything that you ran into.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You were allowed to go in in the morning, ice cold, from the faucet and wash yourself as you could.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this is about, you know, outdoor toilets that you were, you were sitting, also, nothing but toilets.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One day, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] we knew that there, there were only rumors on the next bed to us, that a woman was pregnant because they never allowed it, you know, they never-- if you were pregnant or something.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And during the night, we could hear a muffled scream because she gave birth.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they knew that if they'll know that she gave birth, the Nazis, they'll immediately kill her, so they suffocated the baby.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They made her-- dragged her out in the morning to go to the-- to be counted, zahlappell, it was called.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the baby was-- oh, this was a horror thing because right next to us, it left a horror impression.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] She loved that baby.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Later life, I used to say, I'm not going to have children.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't want ever my children should experience what I experienced.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[CRYING] And this is how it went on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They would come-- when a transport would come in, they would put on the lights.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the lights, if you went five, six feets from the light-- you know, we were surrounded with, like, a barbed, a huge barbed wire with lights.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And a transport came in, and they were going to march.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
